Description: Gibson es 335 vintage. This is a fantastic guitar. I have been the proud owner for 5 years and it has brought me great joy. This 335 came to me as just a husk, so there is no original hardware or pickups. It does have: -500k pots -Classic 57 in neck -Lindy Fralin pure PAF in bridge -StewMac repro trapeeze tail piece -original frets -grover tuning machines. -comes with Gator Hard Case. There was an attempt to thwart a neck reset when a previous owner attached a plate on the heal to the body (shown in pictures). It is holding without it, but probably will need a reset at some point. Frets are original and low, no neck break at all. Previous owner may have painted inside f holes as there are a few yellow spots, but not noticable and easily removable. Never been drilled for a hard tail, but two small holes makes me think a bigsby at one point. Excepting offers!! If you have any questions, please let me know.
Title: 1971 Gibson es 335TD
